# DAC UI Design Guide

All new UI must match the existing game's visual style. The **Pets Inventory panel** (`DAC/Inventory Pets.PNG`) is the canonical reference. Study it before creating or modifying any UI.

Reference screenshots live in `DAC/*.PNG` — always check them before designing.

## Panel Anatomy (mandatory structure)

Every panel follows this exact layout:

1. **Tab bar** (if multi-tab) — White pill-shaped container, centered at top of screen, dark silhouette icons inside. Sits *above* the panel, not inside it.
2. **Title** — Floats above-left of the panel frame, *outside* the border. Colorful icon + bold white text with dark TextStroke. Never inside a title bar.
3. **Close button** — Bright red rounded square, white **✕**, top-right corner of the panel.
4. **Panel body** — Pastel pink-to-lavender background with a subtle watermark pattern (faded silhouettes of content type). Thick dark rounded border (2-3px charcoal/navy). Large corner radius (12-16px).
5. **Content area** — Scrollable grid or list inside the body.
6. **Bottom bar** (if needed) — Action buttons + filter icons + search, pinned at bottom of panel.

## Color Palette

| Role | Color | Notes |
|------|-------|-------|
| Panel background | Pastel pink `#FFD6EE` → lavender `#E0D6FF` | Soft gradient or solid. Subtle watermark pattern overlay |
| Panel border | Dark charcoal `#2A2A40` | Thick (2-3px), UIStroke |
| Close button | Bright red `#FF2222` | White ✕, rounded square, always top-right |
| Positive action | Emerald green `#2ECC71` | "Equip", "Claim", "Rebirth" buttons |
| Negative/toggle off | Red `#FF4444` | "No Pets", disabled toggles |
| Title text | White `#FFFFFF` | Dark TextStroke (black or near-black) |
| Body text | Dark `#1E1E1E` on light panels | Or white with stroke for HUD overlays |
| Currency gold | `#FFD54F` | Coin amounts |
| Currency purple | `#CE93D8` | Crystal/gem amounts |
| Section headers | Gray rounded bar `#CCCCCC` | Bold dark text inside |

## Shape Language

- **Everything is rounded and chunky.** No thin lines, sharp corners, or minimal design.
- Panel corners: `UDim.new(0, 14)` or larger
- Button corners: `UDim.new(0, 8)`
- Card/cell corners: `UDim.new(0, 8)`
- Tab bar: Fully rounded pill (`UDim.new(0.5, 0)`)
- Input fields: Rounded gray border, light fill

## Typography

- **GothamBlack** for panel titles and major headers
- **GothamBold** for buttons, labels, card text, section headers
- **Gotham** for secondary/body text only
- Never use thin, light, or serif fonts
- Titles outside panels: white text + dark TextStroke (Thickness ~2, Color `#000000`)
- All text must be readable at a glance — large sizes, high contrast

## Icons

- **Tab bar icons**: Dark silhouettes on white pill background. No color, no outlines — just solid black shapes.
- **Title icons**: Colorful, emoji-style or rendered 3D-style icons. Each panel has a unique icon (shopping cart for Store, egg for Eggs, paw for Pets, gear for Settings, etc.)
- **Action icons**: Simple dark silhouettes in bottom bars (lock, trash, tag shapes)

## Item Cards (grid cells)

- Light background (white or very light pastel)
- Rounded corners
- Item image fills most of the card
- Name/stat label below the image, bold, dark text
- Equipped items get a green checkmark overlay
- Rarity indicated by subtle border color glow (not text)

## What NOT to do

- Do not use dark/navy backgrounds for panel bodies (that's the code-generated fallback look, not the design target)
- Do not put titles inside the panel frame — they float outside, above-left
- Do not use flat, minimal, or Material Design aesthetics
- Do not use UIGradient for dark-to-darker panel backgrounds
- Do not create small cramped text — everything should feel big, bold, and bubbly
- Do not skip the watermark pattern on panel backgrounds
